  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The goal of this study is to evaluate the interest of second-generation Endocuff Vision (ECV)
      to improve Adenoma detection rate and / or Polyp detection rate in routine colonoscopy.

      This is a prospective comparative cohort, on 1034 patients, 517 patients with ECV in
      prospective group and 517 without ECV in retrospective group
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
